						<h1>Journalism is now the <i>second</i> draft of history</h1>
                        <h2>By James Harkin</h2></a>
                        <p>In the age of the relentless media fact-check, reading the news often feels like hearing a punch-line deflated before you catch the body of the joke. Free-floating fact-checking initiatives have lately become big (non-profit) business. In an industry—the written media—whose...</p>
